Information Bulletin Issued in Democratic Congo 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 25 (KCNA) -- The National Committee for the Study of the Juche Idea of Democratic Congo released an information bulletin titled "The Invincible Workers' Party of Korea" on Sept. 12 on the occasion of the 60th anniversary of the WPK.
 The bulletin in an article gave a detailed account of the fact that the WPK is accelerating the building of a great prosperous powerful nation, increasing the defence capability of the country in every way and demonstrating its might to win sure victory by pursuing the Songun politics guided by the Juche idea, and that it has grown stronger to be a mighty party which has achieved steel-like unity and maintains close ties with the popular masses. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Leader Kim Jong Il formulated the revolutionary idea of President Kim Il Sung as an integral system of idea, theory and method of Juche and steadily developed and enriched it, making the Juche idea the great guiding idea in the era of independence and laying a solid groundwork for strengthening the WPK into an eternal party of the President, the bulletin noted. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il has performed great exploits in the political, military, economic, cultural and all other fields, while guiding all affairs of the Party, the army and the state after beginning his work at the WPK Central Committee, the bulletin said, adding that the WPK will always emerge victorious as it is led by him.

DPRK to Closely Follow How U.S. Will Move at Phase of Action in Future 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 25 (KCNA) -- The DPRK's stand to seek a negotiated solution to the nuclear issue between the DPRK and the U.S. remains consistent. The DPRK government will as ever make patient efforts to realize the denuclearization of the Korean Peninsula.
 Choe Su Hon, vice-minister of Foreign Affairs who is leading the DPRK delegation, declared this when addressing the plenary meeting of the 60th UN General Assembly on Sept. 22. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK participated in the discussion of the issue with magnanimity and sincerity from its principled and fair stand to realize at any cost the denuclearization of the Korean Peninsula, its avowed ultimate goal, at the recent fourth six-party talks held in Beijing, thus making it possible to meet all challenges and reach an agreement on the principle for the denuclearization of the Korean Peninsula in a broad sense, he noted.
 What is most important at this stage is for the U.S. to provide the DPRK with light water reactors as early as possible as evidence proving its substantial recognition of the DPRK's right to nuclear activity for a peaceful purpose, Choe said, adding the DPRK will closely follow how the U.S. will move in actuality at the phase of action in the future. 
 He went on to say: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The UN should be reformed as required by the new century if it is to fulfill its mission for global peace and security and the economic and social progress. What is most important here is to materialize UN-centered multilateralism in line with the purpose and principle of the UN Charter. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The UN Security Council should be reformed on the principle of ensuring full representation of non-aligned countries and other developing countries who account for an absolute majority of the member nations of the UN. Japan should not be allowed under any circumstances to sit on the Security Council as it has refused to redeem the crimes it committed against other countries in the past and has distorted its history of aggression and driven the regional situation to confrontation. 
 Turning to the reform of UN organizations on human rights, he said that this reform should give top priority to putting an end to the infringement upon state sovereignty, politicization of human rights, double standards and selectivity, worst human rights abuses at present, and consider it as an ultimate goal. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 And it is also necessary to strictly observe the principle of ensuring full representation of UN member nations the same way as done in reforming the UNSC, he noted, and stressed: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK government will boost the friendly and cooperative relations with all the countries of the world that respect the sovereignty of the DPRK on the principle of independence, peace and friendship and thus make a positive contribution  to the efforts of the UN member states to build a peaceful and prosperous new world.

Japan's Policy of Toeing U.S. Line under Fire 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 25 (KCNA) -- Japan's policy of toeing the U.S. line is aimed to find a way out under the U.S. patronage and support and attain its sinister purpose, says Rodong Sinmun Sunday in a signed commentary dealing with Japan's policy of toeing the U.S. line that has become all the more undisguised in the new century.
 The strategic goal of Japan's foreign policy in the 21st century is to hold the position of a political and military power in the international arena and exercise its influence, the commentary says, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the U.S. that the Japanese reactionaries believe as savior in attaining such a strategic goal. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan has historically served the U.S. Japan's policy of toeing the U.S. line has become all the more vital and essential today. Japan seeks to obtain permanent membership of the UN Security Council, increase its political position in the international arena and thus become a political giant who exercises tremendous power in the new century. The world considers Japan's bid to be permanent membership of the UNSC as a dangerous attempt to bring another disaster to humankind in the new century. Under this situation the Japanese reactionaries seek to turn the public mindset favorable for themselves with the help of the U.S. and become a permanent member of the SC at any cost. That is why they serve the U.S. actively, meeting its demands. The Japanese reactionaries are persistently pursuing the policy of toeing the U.S. line, obsessed by a foolish ambition that they may reverse the situation and get permanent membership of the SC despite opposition of other countries if the U.S.  helps them.
 Japan is set to emerge a military power and make a decision of permitting a war by law in a few years to come. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan's intensification of its policy of toeing the U.S. line is a dangerous action of inciting confrontation and dispute and sparking off arms race in Asia. Meanwhile, the U.S. is seeking to draw Japan to let it play a shock brigade in executing its Korea, Asia strategy. Japan is seeking to dash forward militarization and overseas expansion under the active patronage of the U.S. Therefore, Japan remains as a root cause of threatening and harassing peace and security in Asia even in the new century just as in the last century. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Asian people are heightening vigilance against Japan's mean and criminal policy of toeing the U.S. line.

U.S. Nuclear Hysteria Assailed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 25 (KCNA) -- The U.S. is contemplating working out new guidelines for the use of nuclear weapons, rejecting the existing ones. So, it intends to go unchallenged in the field of strategic nuclear armed forces in a bid to beat its rivals and mercilessly destroy those countries challenging its bid to establish its order of world domination.
 Minju Joson Sunday observes this in a signed commentary. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. new doctrine on the use of nuclear weapons is of increasingly belligerent and offensive nature, the commentary says, and goes on:
 The U.S. nuclear hysteria based on the nuke-all powerful conception has reached its height and gone far beyond the tolerance limit. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Its modification of the above-said doctrine would be inevitably followed by other powers' reexamination of the regime for the use of nuclear weapons to keep the strategic balance. Then it would be as clear as noonday that this would spark off a nuclear arms race. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This proves that the U.S. is chiefly to blame for posing the threat of nukes to the world and proliferating them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is beyond doubt that such U.S. high-handed and arbitrary practices as wielding its nuclear stick will become more undisguised than ever before. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Such reality eloquently shows what just and wise Songun politics the Workers' Party of Korea has pursued to increase its deterrent for self-defence in every way in order to cope with the daily growing U.S. nuclear threat. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The army and people of the DPRK are proud of having built such self-defensive deterrent strong enough to protect the national dignity and security from the U.S. nuclear threat. The U.S. nuclear stick will not work on the DPRK that has extraordinarily strong spirit of independence and has sufficient self-defensive means in place. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If the U.S. recklessly forces a nuclear war on the DPRK, its army and people will exercise their legitimate right to self-defence as a powerful means of retaliation.
 Nuclear weapons are no longer the monopoly of the U.S. and gone are the days when it considered nukes all-powerful. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. would be well advised to cool its head overheated with nuclear hysteria and face up to the reality.

Int'l Conference Demands Japan's Settlement of Its Past
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 24 (KCNA) -- The Third Conference of the International Solidarity Council Demanding the Settlement of Japan's Past was held here on September 22 and 23.
 Present there were delegations of the north and the south of Korea and delegations of organizations demanding postwar compensation, human rights organizations and overseas Koreans' organizations from China, Taipei of China, Japan, Netherlands, Germany, the United States and other countries and regions.
 Academic and public figures, experts, researchers and officials concerned of the DPRK were present as observers. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Hong Son Ok, chairperson of the Korean Committee of the council, made a keynote report at the conference. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Now is the time to stir up an atmosphere of actions demanding Japan's settlement of its past worldwide as it observed the 60th anniversary of its defeat without taking any practical steps to redress its past crimes, the reporter said. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 She underscored the need to make a thorough-going probe into the truth behind the grisly human rights abuses against humanity committed by Japan and dynamically push ahead with the work to deal with them internationally.
 In this regard it is necessary to conduct in the future activities to request the UN Commission on Human Rights or its Sub-Commission on Human Rights to appoint a special rapporteur who would specialize in surveying and studying the issue of remains of the victims of the forcible drafting by Japan  and continue to probe the issue of those forcibly taken to Japanese enterprises, she said, underscoring the need to make efforts to prevent textbooks in which history is most grossly distorted from being adopted by schools. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 She called for conducting a dynamic campaign to denounce Japanese politicians' visits to the "Yasukuni Shrine" and Japan's moves to grab Tok Islet as well as the issue of distortion of history in textbooks in combination with the struggle against the revision of Japan's constitution and overseas dispatch of the "Self-Defense Forces".
 We will as ever attach importance to unity and cooperation through the international solidarity council and expand the ranks in vast areas of the world in order to widen the scope of the movement, she stressed. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Participants of the conference heard testimonies made by victims of crimes committed by Japan in the past. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Victims of the crimes related to "comfort women" for the imperial Japanese army said that they were deprived of everything by the Japanese imperialists, i.e. something they could enjoy as human beings and young women, adding this mental pain always torment them as unhealable wounds. They demanded the Japanese government make an unconditional apology and compensation for the past crimes.
 Victims of above-said forcible drafting and their bereaved families testified to the facts that the forcible drafting was the thrice-cursed hideous abduction committed by Japan against humanity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The conference involved panel discussions and plenary session. 
 Speeches were made at the panel discussions on the subjects of the issue of the "comfort women" for the imperial Japanese army, the issue of forcible drafting and massacres, the issue of victims to A-bombs, the issue of history distortion, the issue of militarization, the issue of turning Japan Rightist and the issue of remains of the victims of forcible drafting. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The plenary session was informed of the measures for enhancing the function and role of the international solidarity council in order to check and frustrate the Japanese government's base acts of negating its past history of aggression and evading its responsibility for its crimes against humanity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A resolution was adopted at the conference. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It underscored the need to launch a more dynamic movement for probing the truth behind Japan's grisly human rights abuses and demanding their settlement worldwide and conduct a powerful movement against Japan's negating its past crimes and distorting history as an Asian-wide movement in order to shatter such moves without fail. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It also stressed the need to counter the moves of Japan to veer to the Right and its militarization with a powerful peace movement against war.
 In order to carry through the resolution, it is imperative to further expand and strengthen the ranks of the International Solidarity Council Demanding the Settlement of Japan's Past and decisively increase its function and role, the resolution stressed.

S. Korean Authorities' Moves for International Tourism of Tunnel under Fire
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 24 (KCNA) -- A spokesman for the Committee for the Peaceful Reunification of the Fatherland in a statement on Sept. 23 denounced the south Korean authorities' recent moves for international tourism of tunnels as a blatant challenge to the sincere efforts of the DPRK for peace and reunification of the country and as a traitorous act to make money by abusing national division.
 It is self-evident that the authorities' moves to make the tunnels, which they have long used for an anti-north smear campaign, an object of international tourism is aimed to create international public opinion in a bid to tarnish the authority of the dignified DPRK and perpetuate the division of the country into the north and the south, the statement said, and went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We can not but take a serious view of the south Korean authorities' burlesque staged at a time when the north and the south have stopped slandering the other side and removed all propaganda means in the areas along the military demarcation line in the spirit of the June 15 joint declaration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reckless move compels us to think again if the south Korean authorities have true willingness to fundamentally remove the root cause of mistrust and confrontation between the north and the south and implement the June 15 joint declaration.
 For national unity and reunification the south Korean authorities and bellicose forces should unconditionally stop their farce for tourism of the tunnels which lays an obstacle in the implementation of the joint declaration and the improvement of the inter-Korean relations and make a bold decision to remove wire entanglements and concrete wall symbolic of division.

Joint Slogans Serve as Banner of Socialist Cause: Rodong Sinmun
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 24 (KCNA) -- The joint slogans published by the Central Committee and the Central Military Commission of the Workers' Party of Korea on the occasion of its 60th founding anniversary serve as a banner of the world progressive people aspiring after independence and socialism as they clarify the ways of frustrating all the moves of the imperialists for domination and defending and advancing the cause of socialism and independence. 
 Rodong Sinmun Saturday observes this in a signed article. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The joint slogans lay stress on keeping the Juche character and the national character in the revolution and construction, the article says, and goes on:
 Maintaining the Juche character and the national character is a vital matter of deciding the destinies of the country and the nation and an important matter of governing the victory of the cause of socialism and independence.
 The joint slogans clarify the idea that arms are instantly socialism, the sovereignty of the country and a treasure sword for shaping the destiny of the nation and it is the revolutionary spirit of the Korean People's Army to resolutely punish aggressors and provocateurs. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 To reject illusions about imperialism and to carry on the revolution and construction one's way by one's own efforts with one's view, this is the way for every nation to live and achieve prosperity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is important to firmly maintain the fundamental principles of socialism in defending and advancing the cause of socialism. The joint slogans lay stress on maintaining the principles of socialism in all spheres of state activities and social life. 
 It is imperative to maintain the fundamental principles of socialism in order to build and defend socialism in conformity with the independent demand and basic interests of the popular masses. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 What is important here above all is to consolidate the party of the working class organizationally and ideologically and firmly ensure the party's leadership over the revolution and construction. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Strengthening the party and consolidating its role of leadership is a main guarantee for frustrating all moves of the hostile forces against revolution and socialism, strengthening the driving force of revolution and successfully advancing the  revolution and construction. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The function and role of socialist power should be steadily enhanced. 
 The enhanced function and role of socialist power makes it possible to correctly manage socialist society and successfully propel socialist construction. 
 At the same time, it is imperative to resolutely struggle against the imperialists' moves against socialism and independence. The joint slogans also clarify the idea that the all the people aspiring after socialism and independence should wage an anti-imperialist, anti-U.S. struggle. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the consistent policy and will of our party to defend and advance the cause of socialism and independence victoriously in unity with all people of the world who advocate independence, the article concludes. It is clearly reflected in the joint slogans.
